org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions

Class ClassTraitsDefinition

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.DefinitionBase
      • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.ScopedDefinitionBase
        • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.MemberedDefinition
          • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.TypeDefinitionBase
            • org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.definitions.ClassTraitsDefinition
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDefinition, IDocumentableDefinition, IMemberedDefinition, IScopedDefinition, ITypeDefinition, IDefinitionSet

    public final class ClassTraitsDefinition
extends TypeDefinitionBase
    Definition to represent the class traits, which holds all the static members, and whose baseclass is "Class". This is implemented as a wrapper around the existing TypeDefinition - most methods just proxy to the wrapped instance.

      • hasNamespace

        public boolean hasNamespace(INamespaceReference namespace,
                   ICompilerProject project)
        Description copied from interface: IDefinition
        Determines whether the specified namespace is present on this definition.

        Namespaces include public, private, protected, and internal, plus any custom namespaces available in the definition's scope.

        The namespace is specified by an INamespaceReference, which can represent not only a custom namespace like ns1 but also ns1::ns2, (ns1::ns2)::ns3, etc.

        Specified by:
        hasNamespace in interface IDefinition
        Overrides:
        hasNamespace in class DefinitionBase
        Parameters:
        namespace - An INamespaceReference specifying the namespace to check for.
        Returns:
        true if the namespace is present.
